  transform: translateX(-100%);

		function getname(path){			
			path = path.replace(/\/c\/empresas\//g, '/').replace(/\/c\/vf\//g, '/').replace(/\/c\/sp\//g, '/').replace(/\/ca\/c\//g, '/').replace(/\/c\//g, '/').replace(/\/es\//g,'/'); //context, false dkt			
			path = path.substring(1).replace(/\/$/g,'');  //head & trailing slash
			
			if (''=='home' && !path.endsWith('home')) {
				path = path.concat('/home');
			}

			if ('particulares'==''){
				path = 'vodafone'+'/'+path;
			} else if ('particulares' != '' && path.substring(0,path.indexOf('/')) != 'particulares') {
				path = 'particulares/'+path;
			}
			return path.replace('_t_','').replace(/\/\//g,'/').replace(/\/particulares\//g, '/').replace(/\//g, ':').replace(/-/g,' ');	
			
		}
			
		var utag_data = {  
			page_url : window.location.href,
			page_type : '',
			page_channel : 'particulares'.replace(/-/g, ' '),
			page_referrer : window.document.referrer,
			page_display_mode : (window.document.documentElement['clientWidth'] < 969) ? 'responsive' : 'estandar',
			page_platform : 'web:wcs',			
			
			visitor_login_status : 'no logado'
		}; 
		
		var _path = window.location.pathname;
		var _pagename = "vfes:" + getname(_path);
		utag_data['page_name']=_pagename;
		
		if (_path.includes('/ca/')){
			utag_data['page_language']='ca';			
		} else {
			utag_data['page_language']='es';			
		}
		
		var _sections = _pagename.split(':');
		utag_data['page_detail']=_sections[_sections.length-1];
		
		var j=1;
		for (i = 2; i < _sections.length; i++) {
			utag_data['page_section_'+j++]=_sections[i];			
		}

function setConsent() {
  const cookies = document.cookie;
  if (cookies.includes('CONSENTMGR')){
    const parts = document.cookie.split('; CONSENTMGR=');
    const consentmgr = parts.pop().split(';'); 
    if (consentmgr.length>1){
         const c3 = consentmgr[0].split('%7C')[2].split(':')[1];     
         if (c3 == 0) {window.InterfaceX.setSnippetConfig({consent: false});}
         else {window.InterfaceX.setSnippetConfig({consent: true});}
    }
  } else {
     window.InterfaceX.setSnippetConfig({consent: false});
  }
  InterfaceX.search();
}

data-ws10-js="module-with-breadcrumb" data-initialized="true"><nav class="ws10-c-breadcrumb ws10-c-breadcrumb--fullwidth ws10-c-breadcrumb--shown" data-ws10-js="breadcrumb" aria-label="breadcrumb" href="https://www.vodafone.es/c/particulares/es/metaverso-vodafone/" sec_uuid="db5891fb373f">Metaverso Vodafone</a></li><li class="ws10-c-breadcrumb__item"><a class="ws10-c-breadcrumb__link" href="https://www.vodafone.es/c/particulares/es/metaverso-vodafone/privacy-policy-metaverse/" tabindex="-1" aria-current="page" sec_uuid="5ff0841db27b">Privacy Policy Metaverse</a></li></ul></nav><div class="ws10-o-layout ws10-o-layout--vertical-flush"><div class="ws10-o-layout__item ws10-u--1/1 "><div class="ws10-o-wrapper"><span id="divBottom"><div id="1500241871850" class="ws10-u--pt5x"><section data-ws10-module-id="1500241871850" class="ws10-m-text-image "><div class="ws10-m-text-image__content-text ws10-u--1/1 ws10-u--pt0 ws10-u--pb0 ws10-u--pt4x ws10-u--pb4x"><div class="ws10-m-text-image__inner ws10-u--1/1 ws10-u--pt0 ws10-u--pb0"><div class="ws10-u--pb6x"><section class="ws10-c-title-standard ws10-align--left"><h2 class="ws10-c-title-standard__title access"><div style="text-align: center;"><span style="color:#FF0000">Vodafone 5G Reality for the Metaverse - Privacy Policy</span></div></h2></section></div><span class="ws10-m-text-image__paragraph ws10-align--left"><p>This Privacy Policy informs about how Vodafone processes the personal data of Vodafone customers and users who download and use the service through the Vodafone 5G Reality -Metaverse application ("<strong>App</strong>").<br> &nbsp;<br> This Privacy Policy supplement specifically regulates the processing of data when accessing and using the App, as well as when contracting products or services (the "<strong>Product(s) or Service(s)</strong>") and virtual content channels (the "<strong>Content(s)</strong>") of third parties offered on the App.<br> &nbsp;<br> For information on how we process your data for the provision of mobile and fixed communications services, you can refer to our main privacy policy <a href="https://www.vodafone.es/c/conocenos/es/vodafone-espana/quienes-somos/legal-y-regulatorio/politica-de-privacidad-y-cookies/" sec_uuid="8dfb6f3bf370">aqu铆</a>.<br> &nbsp;<br> We take the privacy of our users very seriously. We therefore ask you to read this Privacy Policy carefully, as it contains important information about how we will process your personal data.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Changes to our Privacy Policy</span><br> &nbsp;<br> This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. In any case, whenever we carry out a substantial modification of the Privacy Policy, we will update its content on the official Vodafone 5G Reality website and we will inform you through the usual communication channels.<br> &nbsp;<br> &nbsp;<span style="color:#C00000">Who we are</span><br> &nbsp;<br> We are VODAFONE ESPAA S.A.U., with CIF A-80907397, entity responsible for the commercialization of the App and VODAFONE SERVICIOS S.L. with CIF B-87539284 entity that assumes the billing and charging of the Services contracted by the Client, where appropriate, acting in its own name and on behalf of Vodafone Espa帽a (hereinafter jointly "<strong>Vodafone</strong>").<br> &nbsp;<br> In this Privacy Policy:<br> &nbsp; </p><ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>"<strong>Vodafone</strong>" or "<strong>we</strong>" or "<strong>us</strong>" means Vodafone;</li><li>"<strong>Third Party(ies)</strong>" means someone other than the customer, the user or us; and</li><li>"<strong>Vodafone Group</strong>" means Vodafone Group Plc and any Vodafone or other organization in which Vodafone Group Plc owns more than 15% of the share capital.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br> Our registered office is at Avenida de Am茅rica 115, 28042 Madrid. Our main contact channel for customer service is 607123000. Also, through our Web Site there are different contact channels that we put at your disposal.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">How to contact us</span><br> &nbsp;<br> Your opinion is very important to us. If you have any questions about the App, you can contact us at: 607123000.<br> &nbsp;<br> You can write to us at Avenida de Am茅rica 115, 28042, Madrid or call us at 607123000. Our registered office is located at Avenida de Am茅rica 115, 28042, Madrid, or consult about our privacy policy at dpo-spain@vodafone.com.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Personal information we collect about you</span><br> &nbsp;<br><strong>When is your personal information collected?</strong><br> &nbsp;<br><strong>We collect personal information from you when:</strong><br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>You register for the first time and when you log in through Vodafone ID, a secure authentication method of Vodafone 5G Reality App.</li><li>You contract any Product, Service and/or Content offered through the Vodafone 5G Reality App;</li><li>You contact the customer service team for a query or complaint.</li><li>You participate in a contest, draw or survey;</li></ul> &nbsp;<br><strong>What personal data may we process?</strong><br> &nbsp;<br> The type of information we process is, where applicable:<br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>Name, surname, address, cell phone number, email and user or nickname chosen within the Vodafone 5G Reality App;</li><li>Products, Services and/or Content purchased and the date of purchase;</li><li>The Products, Services and/or Content indicated as favorites;</li><li>Customer service information generated when you contact Vodafone, such as notes or a recording of a call you make to one of our contact centers;</li><li>Billing or amounts paid in the Vodafone 5G Reality App, in the event you contract a Product, Service or Content offered and billed by Vodafone.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br> We collect anonymous and aggregated analytical information about how you use the Vodafone 5G Reality App (sections that generate the most interest, number of sessions, duration of sessions) to improve the experience, troubleshoot problems and optimize the App.<br> &nbsp;<br> We will not collect or process information from minors, or information that can be classified as sensitive for any purpose such as: health, sexual orientation, union membership, political opinions, religion or ethnicity.<br> &nbsp;<br><strong>Vodafone will process your personal data based on:</strong><br> &nbsp;<br><strong>1. The fulfillment of the contract by accepting the Terms of Use of the Vodafone 5G Reality App</strong> and for the purposes of fulfilling the requested requests.<br><strong>2. The legitimate interest of Vodafone</strong>, for example, for fraud prevention, maintaining the security of the App and services, direct marketing and improving our services. Whenever the processing of your personal data is based on legitimate interest we will check that our interest never infringes your rights. Additionally, in some cases, you have the right to object to such processing. For more information, please see the Your Rights section of this Privacy Policy.<br><strong>3. To comply with our legal obligations</strong>, including, for example, our tax and accounting obligations that are subject to strict internal policies (such as retention periods), litigation, and your right to limit the use of your data.<br><strong>4. The consent you give us when Vodafone cannot rely on a different legitimate base</strong>. Consent will always be displayed separately, and you may revoke it at any time.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">How we use your personal information</span><br> &nbsp;<br><strong>1. To allow your access to the 5G Reality Vodafone App, the basis of legitimacy being the execution of the contract.</strong><br> &nbsp;<br> We use your information to allow you access to the Vodafone 5G Reality App, which involves:<br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>Registering for the first time and logging in through Vodafone ID, a secure authentication method of the Vodafone 5G Reality App.</li><li>Enjoying free content that may be offered within the App.</li><li>Invite friends to connect with and enjoy Content together.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br><strong>2. To contract the Products and / or Content offered in the Vodafone 5G Reality App, being the legitimate base the execution of the contract.</strong><br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>To process orders placed for any Product, Service and/or Content of third parties offered on the Vodafone 5G Reality App.</li><li>To attend to your queries through customer service, regarding any doubts or queries you may have and to be able to invoice you.</li><li>Notify you of any changes to the App or services that affect you.</li><li>Resolve any technical problems or incidents you may be experiencing with the use of the App or with respect to any of the Products, Services and/or Content offered; and</li><li>Verify identity.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br><strong>3. Service improvement and fraud prevention, the legitimate base being the legitimate interest of Vodafone.</strong><br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>We collect anonymous, de-identified and aggregated information in order to improve the service we offer. None of this analysis is linked to the user or customer in any way.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br> Sometimes we may need to profile you, for security and fraud purposes. We will process your data in order to protect us and detect possible fraud, protect and detect misuse or damage against the App.<br> &nbsp;<br><strong>4. Marketing &amp; Adaptation of our service to your needs, being the legitimate base the legitimate interest of Vodafone, unless you have granted your permission or consent.</strong><br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>Marketing &amp; Profiling</li></ul><ul style="list-style-type: circle; margin-left: 40px;"><li>If you are a customer or user, Vodafone has a legitimate interest in keeping you informed about the Vodafone 5G Reality App. If you have also contracted any Product, Service and/or Content on the App we may adapt these commercial messages depending on the types of Products, Services and/or Content you have contracted.</li><li>We may send you newsletters, invite you to participate in a survey or inform you about prize draws or contests.</li><li>In addition, if you have given us your permission, we may further personalize these marketing messages using your interactions on the App.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br> If you do not want to continue receiving commercial communications from Vodafone, you can object to the sending of commercial communications following the steps indicated in the section "Your rights".<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">How we share your personal information</span><br> &nbsp;<br> Where applicable, we will share your information with:<br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>Vodafone Group companies primarily for internal reporting purposes, based on Vodafone's legitimate interest. Additionally, in those cases in which you have given us your consent we will share your personal customer data with companies of the Vodafone Group in order to send you offers of Vodafone products and services similar or different to those that you have contracted and that are of your interest, provided by such companies, by any means, including telephone, electronic or digital;</li><li>Payment service providers, based on the execution of the contract;</li><li>Third parties for joint promotions with such third party. Such third parties will be responsible for complying with all applicable privacy laws, if you have authorized us to do so;</li><li>Credit reporting, fraud prevention or business scoring agencies;</li><li>Debt collection agencies;</li><li>Judges and courts, government agencies or other public authorities where required or authorized by law;</li><li>Third parties where such a disclosure is necessary to comply with applicable law or other legal or judicial requirements.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">International Data Transfers</span><br> &nbsp;<br> We may need to transfer your information to other Vodafone Group companies or service providers in countries outside the European Economic Area (EEA). The EEA consists of the countries belonging to the European Union, plus Iceland, Liechtenstein and Norway: they are considered to have equivalent data protection and privacy laws. Such data transfers may occur if our servers (i.e. where we store data) or our service providers are located in non-EEA countries, or if you use our services and products during visits to non-EEA countries.<br> If Vodafone sends your information to a non-EEA country, we will ensure that your information is appropriately protected. We will always ensure that an appropriate contract covering the transfer of data is in place. In addition, if the country is deemed not to have laws equivalent to EU data protection standards, we will ask the third party to enter into a legal agreement that reflects those standards. More information about the standard contractual clauses used by Vodafone as a legal agreement can be found at the following URL Standard Contractual Clauses (SCC) (europa.eu). In addition, if necessary, we will request prior authorization from the Spanish Data Protection Agency to be able to carry out the international transfer.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">How long we keep your personal information</span><br> &nbsp;<br> We will store and process your information to provide you with the requested services and, even thereafter, until any liabilities arising from the provision of such services expire for as long as required by law.<br> &nbsp;<br> We will keep certain personal information for a reasonable period of time after the termination of the relationship with Vodafone in case you decide to use our services again if you have not opted out of receiving any marketing communications from us.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Security of your personal information</span><br> &nbsp;<br> We have specialized security teams that constantly review and enhance our security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, accidental loss, disclosure or destruction.<br> &nbsp;<br> Communications over the Internet (such as e-mails) are not secure unless they have been encrypted. Your communications may pass through any number of countries before being delivered, given the nature of the Internet itself. We cannot accept any liability for unauthorized access to or loss of personal information beyond our control.<br> &nbsp;<br> We will never request any personal information from you over the Internet by any unofficial means of communication. You are responsible for keeping your personal and account information secure and not sharing it with others. If you have any questions, please contact us before providing your information.<br> &nbsp;<br> Our Website may provide links to third party websites. We are not responsible for the security or content of their websites. Please be sure to read the privacy policy and cookie policy of those companies before using or entering personal information on their websites. The same applies to any third-party websites or content that you link to in order to use our products and services.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Your Rights</span><br> &nbsp;<br> Below, we detail how you can exercise your rights associated with the data processed by Vodafone in the Vodafone 5G Reality App.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Right to rectify personal data</span><br> You have the right to rectify information stored about you if it is not accurate. If the information we store needs to be updated, or you think it may be inaccurate, if you are a customer, you can log in to "My Vodafone" to update it.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Right of access to personal data</span><br> You have the right to request a copy of the personal data Vodafone stores about you.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Right to data portability</span><br> You have the right to take the data you have provided to us under certain circumstances. For example, Vodafone assures you will be able to take your data by allowing you to download your invoices, as simply as clicking a button, and in electronic format. To do this, if you are a customer, log in to "My Vodafone" under Permissions and Preferences and go to your billing area.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Right to object to the use of personal data</span><br> You have the right, in certain circumstances, to object to the processing of your personal information by Vodafone.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Right of erasure</span><br> Vodafone processes and retains your information only for as long as we need to. In some circumstances, you have the right to request the deletion of your personal data. This data will be kept blocked and accessible only by certain persons if we need to respond to a claim or to meet our obligations.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Right to limit the processing of your personal data</span><br> You have the right to request the limitation of the processing of your data so that Vodafone can store your data, but not use it. This right can only be exercised in certain circumstances such as:<br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>you inform us of the inaccuracy of your personal data, for as long as we need to verify the accuracy of this;</li><li>the processing is unlawful and you do not want us to erase your personal data;</li><li>you have objected to any processing Vodafone carries out based on legitimate interest, during the period we need to verify that your right prevails over that interest;</li><li>Vodafone no longer needs the personal data for the purposes of processing, but you need them for the formulation, exercise or defense of claims;</li></ul> &nbsp;<br> In addition to the specific means established for each right, you may exercise your rights of access, rectification, erasures, objection, limitation and portability, as well as revoke the consents given, by writing attaching a photocopy of your ID to Vodafone with the reference "<strong>Data Protection- App Vodafone 5G Reality</strong>", to Avenida de America, 115, 28042, Madrid or to the email address derechosprotecciondatos@vodafone.es.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">Opt-out of advertising messages:</span><br> &nbsp;<br> If you no longer wish to receive advertising messages from Vodafone, you may choose to opt-out of all of our advertising communications or certain chosen contact methods. There are several ways to opt-out:<br> &nbsp; <ul style="list-style-type: disc;"><li>Contact our Customer Services team;</li><li>Click on the link at the bottom of a marketing email or text message to unsubscribe;</li><li>If you receive a marketing call, tell the agent you are talking to.</li><li>Disable push notifications in our apps, including commercial messages, at any time. To do this, change the notification settings on your device or uninstall the app;</li><li>Send a writing with a photocopy of your ID to Vodafone with the reference "<strong>Data Protection-App Vodafone 5G Reality</strong>", to Avenida de Am茅rica, 115, 28042, Madrid or to the email address derechosprotecciondatos@vodafone.es.</li><li>If you are a customer, access the Permissions and Preferences tool from "My Vodafone", in its web version and in the app.</li></ul> &nbsp;<br> Opting out of receiving commercial communications does not mean you will no longer receive service-related messages, such as messages informing of order statuses or modifications to our Terms and Conditions (unless we have instructed you otherwise). You will continue to receive commercial communications via push notifications if you do not disable them in your device settings.<br> &nbsp;<br> If you are not a customer of Vodafone you may request your exclusion from commercial campaigns through the web https://darbaja.es, where you can indicate the phone numbers and email you want to exclude from such campaigns. Also, we inform you that you can include your data in the official Robinson list, managed by Adigital in https://www.listarobinson.es/.<br> &nbsp;<br><span style="color:#C00000">How to make a complaint</span><br> &nbsp;<br> If you want to contact us to discuss any of your rights or if you have any complaints about how we use your information, please contact us by calling 607123000 or to the email address derechosprotecciondatos@vodafone.es.<br> &nbsp;<br> Vodafone is adhered to the Autocontrol Mediation Protocol, entity to which the user may refer any claim related to Vodafone in the field of data protection to reach an amicable resolution of the same. See www.vodafone.es for more information. We will do our best to help you, but if you are still not satisfied, you can contact the Spanish Data Protection Agency (www.aepd.es).<p></p></span></div></div></section></div></span></div></div></div></div></div></main></div><div class="MDDfooter"><footer class="vfh-footer" tabindex="-1" data-ws10-js="footer"><p
